<record xmlns='http://www.loc.gov/MARC21/slim'><leader>03186ctmaa22004811a 4500</leader><controlfield tag='001'>6030322</controlfield><controlfield tag='005'>20200927163354.0</controlfield><controlfield tag='008'>100111i14711587xx            000 0 ara d</controlfield><datafield ind1=' ' ind2=' ' tag='035'><subfield code='a'>6030322</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=' ' ind2=' ' tag='040'><subfield code='a'>NjP</subfield><subfield code='c'>NjP</subfield><subfield code='e'>amremm</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1='0' ind2=' ' tag='041'><subfield code='a'>ara</subfield><subfield code='a'>ota</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1='0' ind2='0' tag='245'><subfield code='a'>[Collection of eight Sufi texts].</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=' ' ind2=' ' tag='260'><subfield code='c'>[1471-1587]</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=' ' ind2=' ' tag='300'><subfield code='a'>153 leaves, bound :</subfield><subfield code='b'>paper ;</subfield><subfield code='c'>184 x 137 mm.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=' ' ind2=' ' tag='500'><subfield code='a'>Ms. composite codex.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=' ' ind2=' ' tag='500'><subfield code='a'>Physical description: 19-23 lines per page; written in naskhī script in black on thick laid paper. Chapter titles in red; keywords overlined in red. Many glosses and Persian verses added in the margins. The sixth text, al-Tajrīd, is written in a fine naskhī on thinner paper. A few words smudged, some pages browned, some margins dampstained, and two quires loose.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=' ' ind2=' ' tag='500'><subfield code='a'>Text 2 was copied by Aḥmad ibn Ilyās ibn Ṭūrmush (fol. 31); he may also be the copiest for text 1 as the texts appear to be written by the same hand.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1='8' ind2=' ' tag='520'><subfield code='a'>A rare and largely unpublished collection of Sufi texts, all in Arabic with the exception of text 8, which is in Ottoman Turkish. Pages inbetween texts (fol. 1a-3a, 31b-32a, 51a, 140b-141a, 117b-118a, 150b-153b) include Persian poems on mystical and Shiʻite subjects, entries in Arabic and Ottoman Turkish, and ownership entries.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1='0' ind2=' ' tag='505'><subfield code='a'>1. fol. 3a-28b: Hādhā al-kitāb Waṣāyāyi qudsīyah.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1='8' ind2=' ' tag='505'><subfield code='a'>2. fol. 28b-31a: A treatise on the ten principles for the purification of the soul, by Abū al-Najīb al-Kubrá al-Khīwafī.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1='8' ind2=' ' tag='505'><subfield code='a'>3. fol. 32b-48b: Mishkāt al-miṣbāḥ fī bayān awrād al-masāʾ wa-al-ṣabāḥ.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1='8' ind2=' ' tag='505'><subfield code='a'>4. fol. 49a-50b: A short treatise on the sayings of Shaykh Muḥammad ibn ʻAī al-Bisṭāmī.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1='8' ind2=' ' tag='505'><subfield code='a'>5. fol. 51b-117a: Ḥadāʾiq al-ḥaqāʾiq.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1='8' ind2=' ' tag='505'><subfield code='a'>6. fol. 118b-140a: Kitāb al-Tajrīd fī kalimat al-tawḥīd.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1='8' ind2=' ' tag='505'><subfield code='a'>7. fol. 141b-148b: Asrār Manāqib al-abrār.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1='8' ind2=' ' tag='505'><subfield code='a'>8. fol. 149a-150a: Hāz̲ā Aṭvār-i qalb haft kūnah ast.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=' ' ind2=' ' tag='530'><subfield code='a'>Also available in an electronic version.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=' ' ind2=' ' tag='541'><subfield code='c'>Purchase;</subfield><subfield code='a'>Smitskamp Oriental Antiquarium,</subfield><subfield code='d'>2005/06/29</subfield><subfield code='e'>(2005-144).</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=' ' ind2=' ' tag='546'><subfield code='a'>Arabic.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=' ' ind2=' ' tag='563'><subfield code='a'>Leather binding blind-tooled with floral motifs, with flap; rubbed and front hinge cracked.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=' ' ind2='0' tag='650'><subfield code='a'>Sufism</subfield><subfield code='x'>Doctrines</subfield><subfield code='v'>Early works to 1800.</subfield><subfield code='0'>http://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh2010115027</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=' ' ind2='7' tag='655'><subfield code='a'>Manuscripts, Arabic</subfield><subfield code='y'>15th century.</subfield><subfield code='2'>lcsh</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=' ' ind2='7' tag='655'><subfield code='a'>Manuscripts, Turkish.</subfield><subfield code='2'>lcsh</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1='1' ind2='2' tag='700'><subfield code='a'>Khīwafī, Abū al-Najīb al-Kubrá.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1='1' ind2='2' tag='700'><subfield code='a'>Bisṭāmī, Muḥammad ibn ʻAlī.</subfield><subfield code='t'>Selections.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1='0' ind2='8' tag='774'><subfield code='t'>Hādhā al-kitāb Waṣāyāyi qudsīyah.</subfield><subfield code='w'>6030326</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1='0' ind2='8' tag='774'><subfield code='t'>Mishkāt al-miṣbāḥ fī bayān awrād al-masāʾ wa-al-ṣabāḥ.</subfield><subfield code='w'>6030360</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1='0' ind2='8' tag='774'><subfield code='t'>Ḥadāʾiq al-ḥaqāʾiq.</subfield><subfield code='w'>6030433</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1='0' ind2='8' tag='774'><subfield code='t'>Kitāb al-Tajrīd fī kalimat al-tawḥīd.</subfield><subfield code='w'>6030437</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1='0' ind2='8' tag='774'><subfield code='t'>Asrār Manāqib al-abrār.</subfield><subfield code='w'>6030442</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1='0' ind2='8' tag='774'><subfield code='t'>Hāz̲ā Aṭvār-i qalb haft kūnah ast.</subfield><subfield code='w'>6030797</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1='4' ind2='1' tag='856'><subfield code='u'>http://arks.princeton.edu/ark:/88435/kp78gk711</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=' ' ind2=' ' tag='902'><subfield code='a'>des</